    "summary": "Integer underflow in wolfSSL packet sniffer <= 5.8.4 allows an attacker to cause a buffer overflow...",
    "details": "Integer underflow in wolfSSL packet sniffer <= 5.8.4 allows an attacker to cause a buffer overflow in the AEAD decryption path by injecting a TLS record shorter than the explicit IV plus authentication tag into traffic inspected by `ssl_DecodePacket`. The underflow wraps a 16-bit length to a large value that is passed to AEAD decryption routines, causing heap buffer overflow and a crash. An unauthenticated attacker can trigger this remotely via malformed TLS Application Data records.",
